The paper deals with modeling and inferring social networks, which falls under the category of social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Societal Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques to solve the regression problem, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves statistical modeling and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), respectively.
